    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen cross-compiling with Emscripten, nlua0 is compiled as a WASM binary. However, it is a host build tool that executes on the host machine during the build process. The relevant line in ```src/nvim/CMakeLists.txt`` is:\n```bash\nset(LUA_GEN ${LUA_GEN_PRG} ${GENERATOR_PRELOAD} ${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR} $<TARGET_FILE:nlua0> ${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR})\n```\n\n$<TARGET_FILE:nlua0> always resolves to the target compiled binary (WASM in this case) with no way to override it for cross compilation scenarios.\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Install Emscripten SDK:\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk.git\ncd emsdk\n./emsdk install latest\n./emsdk activate latest\nsource ./emsdk_env.sh\n```\n\n2. Clone Neovim:\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/neovim/neovim.git neovim-wasm\ncd neovim-wasm\n```\n\n3. Attempt to build for WASM:\n```bash\nmkdir build-wasm && cd build-wasm\n\nemcmake cmake .. \\\n  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \\\n  -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=$EMSDK/upstream/emscripten/cmake/Modules/Platform/Emscripten.cmake \\\n  -DPREFER_LUA=ON\n\nemmake make -j$(nproc)\n```\n\n4. Build fails with:\n```\n/usr/bin/lua5.1: error loading module 'nlua0' from file\n  '.../build-wasm/lib/libnlua0.a': invalid ELF header\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim should be buildable for WebAssembly using Emscripten. When cross compiling, the build system, it should use a host native nlua0 binary for code generation, since nlua0 must run on the host machine during the build process and can't be executed as a WASM binary.\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.5 \n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nbuild system issue \n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 24 (WSL2 on Windows)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWSL2 \n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuilt from repo",
