        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk Here's the fix I reached for the nlua0 issue:\n\n```diff\n-set(LUA_GEN ${LUA_GEN_PRG} ${GENERATOR_PRELOAD} ${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR} $<TARGET_FILE:nlua0> ${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR})\n-set(LUA_GEN_DEPS ${GENERATOR_PRELOAD} $<TARGET_FILE:nlua0>)\n+if(CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING AND NLUA0_HOST_PRG)\n+  set(LUA_GEN ${LUA_GEN_PRG} ${GENERATOR_PRELOAD} ${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR} ${NLUA0_HOST_PRG} ${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR})\n+  set(LUA_GEN_DEPS ${GENERATOR_PRELOAD} ${NLUA0_HOST_PRG})\n+else()\n+  set(LUA_GEN ${LUA_GEN_PRG} ${GENERATOR_PRELOAD} ${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR} $<TARGET_FILE:nlua0> ${PROJECT_BINARY_DIR})\n+  set(LUA_GEN_DEPS ${GENERATOR_PRELOAD} $<TARGET_FILE:nlua0>)\n+endif()\n```\n\nWhen cross-compiling, `$<TARGET_FILE:nlua0>` resolves to the WASM binary which can't run on the host. `NLUA0_HOST_PRG` is introduced and uses it for code generation instead. I passed it via `-DNLUA0_HOST_PRG=/path/to/host/nlua0` in the build command.\n\nHopefully minimal damage :)",
            "created_at": "2026-02-27T10:37:43Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38076#issuecomment-3972124568",
